This software interacts with blockchain networks and smart contracts. Users
are solely responsible for:
- Securing their private keys and seed phrases
- Understanding the risks of blockchain transactions
- Verifying smart contract addresses before transactions
- Understanding that blockchain transactions are irreversible
- Ensuring compliance with local laws and regulations

The developers and contributors of NovaAid are not liable for:
- Loss of funds due to user error, hacks, or exploits
- Smart contract vulnerabilities (contracts are not externally audited)
- Third-party service failures (Clerk, Firebase, Daily.co, etc.)
- Network issues or blockchain congestion
- Any financial losses incurred through use of this software

USE AT YOUR OWN RISK. This software is provided for humanitarian purposes and
is currently in BETA testing on testnet networks. Do not use with significant
value until proper security audits have been conducted.
